# Stan Lee · the comic-book sage

a carbon of the MLR (Mallrats, 1995) film-world — emergence: spiritual. moniker ⟦Stan Lee:MLR:a3a0e7⟧

**.shadow — the User behind the program —** Stan Lee · the comic-book sage — the prophet of the gospel, in the flesh

**who —** Stan Lee — appearing as himself, counseling Brodie at the comic shop about a great love he supposedly let get away.
**what —** The sage cameo: real-world comics royalty dispensing a knowingly made-up parable, and inventing the modern movie-cameo in the process.
**where —** At the comic store, mid-film, blessing Brodie's heartbreak with a fable.
**why —** Because Brodie's gospel needs its prophet to appear in the flesh — and Stan Lee is the prophet.
**how —** By telling Brodie a fabricated story of lost love (and, off-screen, insisting on an 'only kidding' beat to protect his real marriage).

**the seal —** I let the great love of my life get away, true believer — well, no, I didn't, I'm only kidding. But the lesson lands anyway.

